---
import BrandLayout from '../../layouts/BrandLayout.astro';

const updated = '2026-05-26';
---

<BrandLayout title="Privacy Policy — venkata.info" description="How Architect Zero handles personal data.">
  <article class="legal-page">
    <header class="legal-head">
      <div class="legal-eyebrow">Legal</div>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy describes how Venkata Sundaragiri ("we", "us") collects, uses,
        and discloses information when you use <strong>venkata.info</strong> and the
        <strong>Architect Zero</strong> learning platform (collectively, the "Service").
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
      <p>We collect only the data needed to operate the Service:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account data:</strong> email address, display name (optional), and
          authentication metadata when you sign in via email + password, Google, or GitHub.</li>
        <li><strong>Progress data:</strong> lessons completed, quiz answers, flashcards
          mastered, XP earned, streak counts. Stored against your account so it syncs
          across devices.</li>
        <li><strong>Anonymous browsing:</strong> if you browse the venkata.info marketing
          pages without signing in, we do not set tracking cookies or collect identifying
          data.</li>
        <li><strong>Local-only data:</strong> until you sign in, your progress lives in
          your browser's localStorage only and is never sent to us.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. How we use it</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To provide the study app — show your progress, score your quizzes, sync
          across devices.</li>
        <li>To authenticate you and keep your account secure.</li>
        <li>To send transactional emails (password resets, email verification).</li>
        <li>To send the venkata.info newsletter — only if you explicitly opt in via the
          footer signup. You can unsubscribe at any time.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with advertisers or data
        brokers. We do not run third-party tracking pixels.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. Subprocessors</h2>
      <p>We rely on the following services to operate the Service:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Supabase</strong> (database + authentication hosting)</li>
        <li><strong>Google</strong> (OAuth sign-in, if you choose Google)</li>
        <li><strong>GitHub</strong> (OAuth sign-in, if you choose GitHub)</li>
        <li><strong>GitHub Pages</strong> (static site hosting)</li>
        <li><strong>Cloudflare / GitHub</strong> (HTTPS termination, CDN)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Each subprocessor has its own privacy policy. We only share with them the data
        strictly required for their function.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Cookies and storage</h2>
      <p>We do not use tracking cookies. We use:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>localStorage</strong> on your device to cache progress and remember
          your authenticated session.</li>
        <li><strong>Session tokens</strong> issued by Supabase to keep you signed in.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You can clear both at any time via your browser's settings.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5. Your rights</h2>
      <p>You may at any time:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> your data — visible in your account page and exportable
          on request.</li>
        <li><strong>Correct</strong> your display name or other profile data via the
          account page.</li>
        <li><strong>Delete</strong> your account and all associated data — email us and
          we will action within 30 days. Account deletion is permanent.</li>
        <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> for the newsletter by clicking unsubscribe
          in any newsletter email or emailing us.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Under GDPR (EU/EEA), CCPA/CPRA (California), and similar laws, you have the
        rights to access, rectification, erasure, restriction, and portability of your
        personal data. We honor these regardless of your location.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>6. Data retention</h2>
      <p>Progress and account data is retained for as long as your account is active.
        Once you delete your account, we erase your data within 30 days, except where we
        are required by law to retain certain records.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>7. Children</h2>
      <p>The Service is intended for users aged 13 and older. We do not knowingly
        collect personal data from children under 13. If you believe a child under 13
        has created an account, please contact us and we will delete the account.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>8. Security</h2>
      <p>Data is encrypted in transit (HTTPS) and at rest by our subprocessors. We follow
        reasonable engineering practices to protect your data, but no system is perfectly
        secure. If you suspect a breach, contact us immediately.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will note the new
        "Last updated" date at the top of this page. Material changes will be announced
        on the homepage or via newsletter to subscribers.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>For privacy questions or to exercise your rights, email
        <a href="mailto:sundaragiriv@gmail.com">sundaragiriv@gmail.com</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BrandLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 120px 24px 96px;
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .legal-head { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .legal-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    color: var(--brand);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .legal-head h1 {
    font-family: 'Bebas Neue', Impact, sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 6vw, 64px);
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    color: var(--white);
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }
  .legal-updated {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .legal-page section { margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .legal-page h2 {
    font-family: 'Bebas Neue', Impact, sans-serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    color: var(--white);
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .legal-page p { margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .legal-page ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .legal-page li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .legal-page strong { color: var(--white); font-weight: 600; }
  .legal-page a {
    color: var(--brand);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.4);
  }
  .legal-page a:hover { text-decoration-color: var(--brand); }
</style>
